Sentencas: The effects of anode porosity on thermal stress and failure probability of a planar solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) are investigated by finite element method (FEM).
Titulo: Effects of anode porosity on thermal stress and failure probability of planar solid oxide fuel cell with bonded compliant seal

Sentencas: The thermal stress and failure probability in planar SOFC with and without considering porosity (CP) were compared.
Titulo: Effects of anode porosity on thermal stress and failure probability of planar solid oxide fuel cell with bonded compliant seal

Sentencas: The results show that the compressive stresses are generated in the electrolyte layer, while tensile stresses are generated in Ag-CuO and BNi2 layer because of the compatibility of deformation.
Titulo: Effects of anode porosity on thermal stress and failure probability of planar solid oxide fuel cell with bonded compliant seal

Sentencas: In the case of considering anode porosity, the compressive stresses in anode and electrolyte layer and the tensile stresses in cathode layer are all decreased.
Titulo: Effects of anode porosity on thermal stress and failure probability of planar solid oxide fuel cell with bonded compliant seal

Sentencas: Comparing to without CP, the thermal stress with CP in electrolyte and cathode layer decreases by 33.2% and 46.9%, respectively.
Titulo: Effects of anode porosity on thermal stress and failure probability of planar solid oxide fuel cell with bonded compliant seal

Sentencas: The anode layer has a large risk of failure (5.6489 x 10(-4)) than that of cathode and electrolyte layer at as-fabricated state.
Titulo: Effects of anode porosity on thermal stress and failure probability of planar solid oxide fuel cell with bonded compliant seal

Sentencas: And the failure probability at cathode layer at start-up reaches 0.998.
Titulo: Effects of anode porosity on thermal stress and failure probability of planar solid oxide fuel cell with bonded compliant seal

Sentencas: The failure probability decreases gradually in the period of creep.
Titulo: Effects of anode porosity on thermal stress and failure probability of planar solid oxide fuel cell with bonded compliant seal

Sentencas: The failure probability in anode, cathode and electrolyte layer with CP all decrease comparing to without CP.
Titulo: Effects of anode porosity on thermal stress and failure probability of planar solid oxide fuel cell with bonded compliant seal

Sentencas: The porosity of anode could lead to the decrease of tensile thermal stress, resulting in the decrease of failure probability in cathode layer.
Titulo: Effects of anode porosity on thermal stress and failure probability of planar solid oxide fuel cell with bonded compliant seal

Sentencas: The reduction speed of failure probability at creep stage with CP is bigger than that without CP.
Titulo: Effects of anode porosity on thermal stress and failure probability of planar solid oxide fuel cell with bonded compliant seal

Sentencas: As the increase of porosity, the failure probability decreases due to the decrease of the tensile stress.
Titulo: Effects of anode porosity on thermal stress and failure probability of planar solid oxide fuel cell with bonded compliant seal
